Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Database permission errors

Solution: Ensure database file has correct ownership: sudo chown www-data:www-data assessment.db
Issue: Apache not serving survey

Solution: Check Apache status: sudo systemctl status apache2 and restart if needed
Issue: Python import errors

Solution: Verify packages installed: pip3 list | grep -E "pandas|matplotlib"
Issue: Empty survey responses

Solution: Check PHP error log: sudo tail -f /var/log/apache2/error.log
Conclusion
This lab introduced the fundamentals of human risk assessment in cybersecurity. Students learned to:

Design and implement a risk assessment framework
Create data collection instruments using web technologies
Store and manage assessment data in a database
Develop scoring algorithms for risk quantification
Generate visual reports for risk communication
These skills form the foundation for comprehensive security awareness programs and human-centered risk management strategies. In subsequent labs, students will expand on this framework to include advanced analytics, automated reporting, and integration with security information systems.
